  "original_title": "\u0b95\u0bca\u0bb4\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bc2\u0ba9\u0bc8 \u0bae\u0bb2\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bb4\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b89\u0ba3\u0bb5\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Food served with cat feces in Colombo",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A case has been registered against 8 persons for running restaurants unfit for human consumption during an inspection of the restaurants under the division of the Sanitary Officer of the Fort Municipal Council of Sri Jayawardenapura.",
        "On the 28th, inspection activities were carried out in about 30 restaurants.",
        "At the same time, health officials found cat feces in the kitchen of a popular restaurant in Rajagiriya and took steps to file a case against the restaurant.",
        "And the eight suspects charged in the roundup have been produced in Colombo, Alutkadai and Gangodawila courts.",
        "During the inspection, health officials observed that meat and fish were stored in refrigerators along with cooked food in some stores. (R)"
      ],
